Abstract = {Recent advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), particularly in
   natural language processing (NLP), have led to the development of
   sophisticated chatbots like ChatGPT. These chatbots excel in answering
   questions and can significantly improve the learning experience by
   providing immediate feedback and support to students. They enable
   continuous learning outside traditional classrooms by understanding and
   responding to questions with human-like proficiency. However, their
   responses are limited to the information they were trained on. In this
   study, we employ the Retrieval-Augmented Generation technique to enable
   these chatbots to access and retrieve relevant information from external
   knowledge sources (such as course material) to improve the generation
   capabilities of these models as virtual teaching assistants.},
