   Analytics-ICCCBDA-Annual, Chengdu, PEOPLES R CHINA, APR 24-26, 2025},
Abstract = {This study introduces an innovative framework that aligns LLM-based AI
   agents with enterprise needs by integrating dual-process theory and
   resource-based task complexity models. Utilizing large language models
   and Retrieval-Augmented Generation, our system simulates diverse task
   and decision-making scenarios through a Strategy Generator and
   Evaluator. The results reveal that decision styles-Rational/Intuitive
   and Participative/Autonomous-vary in performance according to task
   demands, with effective knowledge management further boosting outcomes.
   This framework advances efficient AI integration in enterprise settings,
   enhancing both decision flexibility and execution efficiency.},
