Note = {29th European Symposium on Research in Computer Security (ESORICS),
   Bydgoszcz, POLAND, SEP 16-20, 2024},
Abstract = {Security Systems Assurance (SSA) is crucial as digital threats evolve
   and cybersecurity becomes more complex. Recent advancements in large
   language models (LLMs) have opened new avenues for enhancing SSA
   strategies. These models offer sophisticated data analysis and
   argumentation capabilities that were previously unattainable. Leveraging
   these capabilities, our paper introduces an innovative tool powered by
   LLMs that automates the generation of security assurance profiles by
   interpreting standards and security requirements specific to systems. We
   conducted a case study to compare the effectiveness of this LLM-powered
   tool against traditional methods managed by human experts. The results
   show that our automated tool's performance closely matches that of human
   experts, highlighting the potential of LLMs to transform SSA processes
   and significantly improve the efficiency and reliability of
   cybersecurity defenses.},
