   DEC 15-19, 2025},
Organization = {Acm},
Abstract = {Mathematical content is a foundational component of science, technology,
   engineering, and mathematics (STEM) literatures; yet despite its
   centrality, mathematics faces challenges in digital libraries and search
   systems. This demonstration introduces MathMex-V2, a novel large
   language model (LLM) enabled math search engine, which is aimed at
   addressing these challenges through a broader content coverage, enhanced
   retrieval capabilities, and search interface. While several user
   interface features such as PDF reader, audio search, and hybrid keyboard
   (for text and formula entries) are added, the search quality is also
   enhanced by enabling users to enhance their initial queries through
   LLM's response. Additionally, selective Retrieval Augmented Generation
   (RAG) and query rewriting, and MMR-based diversification are used in the
   retrieval process, thus providing results that are more relevant,
   complete, and in-depth.},
