Year = {2024},
Note = {9th Southern Power Electronics Conference, Brisbane, AUSTRALIA, DEC
   02-05, 2024},
Abstract = {The paper reveals the potential applications of the ChatGPT in power
   electronics. By analyzing academic articles and other relevant
   materials, ChatGPT can efficiently summarize key concepts and then apply
   knowledge in power electronics design. To highlight its uses in the
   autonomous design application, two customized generative pre-trained
   transformers (GPTs) are developed with a retrieval-augmented generation
   (RAG) framework to select the optimal topology and design the system's
   parameters with the predefined specifications. Furthermore, the coding
   ability is assessed to generate the executable codes within a Simulink
   function block, realizing the maximum power point tracking (MPPT)
   algorithm for a boost converter in a photovoltaic application scenario.
   The effectiveness of the designed function is verified through the
   simulation waveforms. Finally, the paper discusses ChatGPT's advanced
   ability for textual analyses. After giving a published paper, some
   challenges with corresponding solutions are proposed by the chatbot.
   Through these demonstrations, this paper offers new sights to
   revolutionize design methodologies.},
