   COMPUTING ENGINEERING, ICETRAN},
Year = {2025},
Note = {12th International Conference on Electrical, Electronic and Computing
   Engineering-IcETRAN, Cacak, SERBIA, JUN 09-12, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc; University of
   Pristina},
Abstract = {Chatbots powered by large language models offer a scalable solution to
   support multiple sclerosis patients by providing accurate, empathetic,
   and personalized responses to their questions. By incorporating
   retrieval-augmented generation (RAG) and domain-specific medical data,
   the chatbot can offer upto-date and evidence-based guidance. The goal of
   this paper is to present the development of an AI-driven healthcare
   solution - a well-optimized chatbot, accessible and reliable as a unique
   helping hand for multiple sclerosis patients, complementing traditional
   medical care. The development of a large language model (LLM)-powered
   chatbot designed specifically to support individuals with multiple
   sclerosis is presented. The developed chatbot aims to assist users in
   tracking symptoms, generating pertinent questions for consultations with
   neurologists, and distinguishing between urgent and non-urgent symptoms.
   However, the paper also identified several critical challenges that
   necessitate ongoing oversight, including ensuring medical accuracy and
   reliability of the chatbot's outputs, addressing ethical concerns
   related to patient data and decision-making, and maintaining empathetic
   and contextually appropriate responses.},
